aa(lp11
VThere are about 10,000 species of ants.
p12
aVThey all live in colonies consisting of one or a few queens,
p13
aVand then all the ants you see walking around are sterile female workers.
p14
aVAnd all ant colonies have in common that there's no central control.
p15
aVNobody tells anybody what to do.
p16
aVThe queen just lays the eggs. There's no management.
p17
aVNo ant directs the behavior of any other ant.
p18
aVAnd I try to figure out how that works.
p19
aVAnd I've been working for the past 20 years
p20
aVon a population of seed-eating ants in southeastern Arizona.
