VAnd then the newly mated queens fly off somewhere, drop their wings,
p55
aVdig a hole and go into that hole and start laying eggs.
p56
aVAnd they will live for 15 or 20 years, continuing to lay eggs
p57
aVusing the sperm from that original mating.
p58
aVSo the queen goes down in there.
p59
aVShe lays eggs, she feeds the larvae \u2014 so an ant starts as an egg, then it's a larva.
p60
aVShe feeds the larvae by regurgitating from her fat reserves.
p61
aVThen, as soon as the ants \u2014 the first group of ants \u2014 emerge,
p62
aVthey're larvae. Then they're pupae. Then they come out as adult ants.
p63
aVThey go out, they get the food, they dig the nest,
